file descriptor		Abbreviation		Description
	0		STDIN			Standard input
	1		STDOUT			Standard output
	2		STDERR			Standard error
____
STDIN : standard input to the shell (typed into terminal)
STDOUt : standard output for the shell ( shown in terminal)
STDERR : Handle error message (location where shell ssends error message generated by the shell or programs and scripts running in the shell

Symbol
- Write   : >
- Append  : >>
- 

##### Redirection output in scripts
Two methods for redirecting output in the script:
 * temporary redirecting each line
 * permanently redirecting all commands in the script

